ins-previews-dec-5-com-155788</ref>\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[King Lear]]'' || [[Leir of Britain|King Lear]] || [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]], Off-Broadway ||<ref>http://www.playbill.com/article/cast-set-for-bam-debut-of-donmars-king-lear-with-derek-jacobi-com-177467</ref>\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Romeo and Juliet (play)|Romeo and Juliet]]'' || [[Mercutio]] || [[Garrick Theatre]], West End || <ref>https://londonist.com/2016/05/derek-jacobi-shamelessly-steals-the-show-in-branagh-s-romeo-and-juliet</ref>\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n* 1985: Commander of the [[Order of the British Empire]] (United Kingdom)\n* 1989: Knight 1st class of the [[Order of the Dannebrog]] ([[Denmark]])<ref name=britannica/>\n* 1994: [[Knight Bachelor]], for services to Drama (United Kingdom)<ref>{{London Gazette| issue=53527 |page=2 | date=30 December 1993 }}</ref>\n\n==Awards and Nominations==\n;Theatre\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category \n!Nominated work\n!Result\n|-\n|1980\n|[[Drama Desk Award]] \n|[[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actor in a Play|Outstanding Actor in a Play]]\n|''[[The Suicide (play)|The Suicide]]''\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1983\n|[[Laurence Olivier Award]]\n|[[Laurence Olivier Award for Actor of the Year in a Revival|Best Actor in a Revival]]\n|''[[Cyrano de Bergerac (play)|Cyrano de Bergerac]]''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1983\n|[[Critics' Circle Theatre Awards]]\n|[[Critics' Circle Theatre Awards#Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n|''[[Cyrano de Bergerac (play)|Cyrano de Bergerac]]'' <br/>''[[Much Ado About Nothing]]''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1983\n|[[Evening Standard Awards]] \n|[[Evening Standard Awards|Best Actor]]\n|''[[Much Ado About Nothing]]''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1984\n|[[Tony Award]]\n|[[Tony Award for Best Actor in a Play|Best Actor in a Play]]\n|''[[Much Ado About Nothing]]''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1985\n|[[Drama Desk Award]]\n|[[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actor in a Play|Outstanding Actor in a Play]]\n|''[[Much Ado About Nothing]]'' <br/>''[[Cyrano de Bergerac (play)|Cyrano de Bergerac]]'' \n|{{nom