es)|Mr Pye]]'' || Mr. Pye || 4 episodes\n|-\n| 1987 || ''[[The Secret Garden (1987 film)|The Secret Garden]]'' || Archibald Craven || Television film\n|-\n| 1988 || ''[[The Tenth Man (1988 film)|The Tenth Man]]'' || The Imposter || Television film\n|-\n| 1990 || ''[[The Civil War (TV series)|The Civil War]]'' || Various || 9 episodes\n|-\n| 1993 || ''[[The World of Peter Rabbit and Friends]] '' || Mr Jeremy Fisher|| 1 episode\n|-\n| 1994\u201398 || ''[[Cadfael (TV series)|Cadfael]]'' || [[Brother Cadfael]] || 13 episodes\n|-\n| 1996 || ''[[Breaking the Code (TV movie)|Breaking the Code]]'' || [[Alan Turing]] || Television film\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[The Wyvern Mystery]]'' || Squire Fairfield || Television film\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Jason and the Argonauts (miniseries)|Jason and the Argonauts]]'' || Phineas || Television film\n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[Frasier]]'' || Jackson Hedley || Episode: \"The Show Must Go Off\"\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2002 || ''[[The Jury (TV serial)|The Jury]]'' || George Cording QC || 6 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[The Edwardian Country House]]'' || The Narrator || All episodes\n|-\n| ''[[The Gathering Storm (2002 film)|The Gathering Storm]]'' || [[Stanley Baldwin]] || Television film\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[London (TV series)|London]]'' || [[Tacitus]] || Television film\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Jake Arnott#Works|The Long Firm]]'' || Lord Edward Thursby || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Agatha Christie's Marple|Marple]]'' || Colonel Protheroe ||Episode: \"[[The Murder at the Vicarage#Television adaptations|The Murder at the Vicarage]]\"\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[The Old Curiosity Shop (2007 film)|The Old Curiosity Shop]]'' || Grandfather || Television film\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Doctor Who]]'' || [[Master (Doctor Who)|The Master]] / Professor Yana || Episode: \"[[Utopia (Doctor Who)|Utopia]]\"\n|-\n| 2007\u201309 || ''[[Mist: The Tale of a Sheepdog Puppy]]'' || Narrator || 38 episodes\n|-\n| 2007\u201309 || ''[[In the Night Garden...]]'' || Narrator || 100 episodes\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[The Borgias (2011 TV series)|The Borgias]]'' || Cardinal Orsini || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Titanic: Blood and Steel]]'' || [[William Pirrie, 1st Viscount Pirrie|William Pirrie]] || 12 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\u2014present || ''[[Last Tango in Halifax]]'' || Alan Buttershaw || 5 series - 24 episodes, [[BBC]]\n|-\n| 2013\u201316 || ''[[Vicious (TV series)|Vicious]]'' || Stuart Bixby || 2 series - 14 episodes, [[PBS]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Grace of Monaco (film)|Grace of Monaco]]'' || Count D'Aillieres || Television film, [[HBO]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[The Amazing World of Gumball]]'' || Moon || Episode: Night\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Inside No. 9]]'' || Dennis Fulcher || Episode: The Devil of Christmas \n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2018 miniseries)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]'' || Bishop || Episode: #1.1 \n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[Good Omens (TV series)|Good Omens]]'' || [[Metatron]] || Episode: Saturday Morning Funtime\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[The Crown (TV series)|The Crown]]'' || [[Edward, Duke of Windsor|Duke of Windsor]] || Episode: Dangling Man\n|}\n\n==Theatre==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Venue !! Ref.\n|-\n| 1959 || ''[[Henry IV, Part 2]]'' || Henry, Prince of Wales || [[Cambridge Arts Theatre]], London || <ref>http://www.abouttheartists.com/artists/306258-derek-jacobi</ref>\n|-\n| 1959 || ''[[Love's Labour's Lost]]'' || Bertram Berowne || [[Lyric Theatre, London|Lyric Opera House]], London || <ref>http://www.abouttheartists.com/artists/306258-derek-jacobi</ref>\n|-\n| 1959 || ''Saint's Day'' || Giles Aldus || [[ADC Theatre]], London || <ref>http://www.abouttheartists.com/artists/306258-derek-jacobi</ref>\n|-\n| 1960 || ''[[Cymbeline]]'' || Iachimo || [[Cambridge Arts Theatre]], London || <ref>http://www.abouttheartists.com/artists/306258-derek-jacobi</ref>\n|-\n| 1960 || ''[[The Duenna]]'' || Ferdinand || [[ADC Theatre]], London || <ref>http://www.abouttheartists.com/artists/306258-derek-jacobi</ref>\n|-\n| 1960 || ''[[Friar Bacon and Friar Bungay]]'