ov/rr/program/bib/clay/ Henry Clay: A Resource Guide] from the Library of Congress\n* {{Gutenberg author|id=Clay,+Henry|name=Henry Clay}}\n* {{Internet Archive author|sname=Henry Clay}}\n* {{Librivox author|id=8682}}\n* [https://bioguideretro.congress.gov/Home/MemberDetails?memIndex=C000482| ''Henry Clay'' - [[Biographical Directory of the United States Congress]]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110202214223/http://elections.lib.tufts.edu/aas_portal/index.xq A New Nation Votes: American Election Returns 1787\u20131825] For Henry Clay's election results.\n* [http://mms.newberry.org/xml/xml_files/Clay.xml Henry Clay Letters, 1825\u20131851] at [[the Newberry Library]]\n* [http://www.familytales.org/results.php?tla=hec Letters of Henry Clay]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121108155451/http://teachingamericanhistory.org/library/index.asp?document=605 Abraham Lincoln's Eulogy of Henry Clay] at [http://teachingamericanhistory.org/ Teaching American History.Org]\n* {{C-SPAN|henryclay}}\n** [http://www.c-span.org/video/?301268-1/henry-clay-presidential-contender \"Henry Clay, Presidential Contender\"] from [[C-SPAN]]'s ''[[The Contenders]]''\n* [http://exploreuk.uky.edu/catalog/xt78pk06x73c/guide Guide to the Henry Clay Letters, 1801\u20131843] housed at the University of Kentucky Libraries Special Collections Research Center\n* [http://exploreuk.uky.edu/catalog/xt751c1thm3n Guide to the Henry Clay Memorial Foundation papers] housed at the University of Kentucky Libraries Special Collections Research Center\n* [https://exploreuk.uky.edu/catalog/xt75dv1cng2m Guide to the Henry Clay account book], housed at the University of Kentucky Libraries Special Collections Research Center\n* {{Wikisource-inline|list=\n** {{cite NSRW|wstitle=Clay, Henry|short=x|noicon=x}}\n** {{cite Appletons'|last=Schurz|first=Carl|wstitle=Clay, Henry|notaref=x|year=1900|short=x|noicon=x}}\n** Carl Schurz. ''[[s:Life of Henry Clay|Life of Henry Clay]]'', 2 vols., 1899.\n** {{cite EB9|wstitle=Clay, Henry|volume=5|short=x|noicon=x}}\n}}\n\n==Popular Culture==\n[[George Pope Morris|George Pope Morris]] and [[Henry Russell (musician)|Henry Russell]] wrote [https://imslp.org/wiki/A_Song_for_the_Man_(Russell%2C_Henry) A Song for the Man] in 1844 as a campaign song for Clay.\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Henry Clay succession and navigation boxes\n|state     = collapsed\n|list1=\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-sen}}\n{{US Senator succession box\n| before    = [[John Adair]]\n| state     = Kentucky\n| class     = 3\n| alongside = [[Buckner Thruston]]\n| years     = November 19, 1806 \u2013 March 3, 1807\n| after     = [[John Pope (Kentucky politician)|John Pope]]}}\n{{s-bef|before= [[Thomas Worthington (governor)|Thomas Worthington]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of youngest members of the United States Congress|Baby of the U.S. Senate]]|years= December 29, 1806 \u2013 March 4, 1807}}\n{{s-aft|after= [[James Fenner]]}}\n{{US Senator succession box\n| before    = [[Buckner Thruston]]\n| state     = Kentucky\n| class     = 2\n| alongside = [[John Pope (Kentucky politician)|John Pope]]\n| years     = January 10, 1810 \u2013 March 3, 1811\n| after     = [[George M. Bibb]]}}\n\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{US House succession box\n| before    = [[William T. Barry]]\n| state     = Kentucky\n| district  = 5\n| years     = March 4, 1811 \u2013 March 3, 1813\n| after     = [[Samuel Hopkins (congressman)|Samuel Hopkins]]}}\n{{US House succession box\n| before    = [[Samuel McKee (1774)|Samuel McKee]]\n| state     = Kentucky\n| district  = 2\n| years     = March 4, 1813 \u2013 January 19, 1814\n| after     = [[Joseph H. Hawkins]]}}\n{{US House succession box\n| before    = [[Joseph H. Hawkins]]\n| state     = Kentucky\n| district  = 2\n| years     = October 30, 1815 \u2013 March 3, 1821\n| after     = [[Samuel H. Woodson (Kentucky)|Samuel Woodson]]}}\n{{US House succession box\n| before    = [[John Telemachus Johnson|John Johnson]]\n| state     = Kentucky\n| district  = 3\n| years     = March 4, 1823 \u201